17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 4020, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 4020. This act shall be known and may be cited as the
21 "Oklahoma Route 66 Centennial Forward Commission Act".
22 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 4020.1, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
Req. No. 16828 Page 1

1 Section 4020.1. Route 66 is one of the original highways within
2 the U.S. Highway System. Officially, the numerical designation 66
3 was assigned to the Chicago-to-Los Angeles route on November 11,
4 1926. From the outset, public road planners intended U.S. 66 to
5 connect the main streets of rural and urban communities along its
6 course for the most practical of reasons; most small towns had no
7 prior access to a major national thoroughfare. This was certainly
8 true in Oklahoma. Oklahoma's stretch of Route 66 runs from Miami
9 through Tulsa and Oklahoma City to Erick, passing through cities and
10 towns of all sizes and vast expanses of rural landscape, before
11 entering Texas and continuing on its way to Santa Monica,
12 California. The Oklahoma Route 66 Centennial Forward Commission is
13 established to plan, coordinate and implement programs and special
14 events to celebrate the historic highway's centennial in 2026 with
15 the support of the Oklahoma Historical Society.
16 The centennial is an opportunity to celebrate the important
17 history of Route 66 in Oklahoma through commemorative, educational
18 and community events, including programs and exhibits about the
19 history of how local communities grew and changed with construction
20 of the highway; the development of a modern transportation system;
21 the cultural impact of Route 66 both within the United States and
22 internationally; the portrayal of Route 66 in music, artwork and
23 folklore; and how we maintain the mystique and appeal of Route 66
24 for future generations.
Req. No. 16828 Page 2

1 The study, preservation and maintenance of Route-66-related
2 resources has been a public/private partnership in Oklahoma for
3 decades. Government agencies, private organizations and individual
4 citizens have played critical roles in these efforts, and the
5 Oklahoma Route 66 Centennial Forward Commission shall seek input
6 from these partners and the general public as it develops plans for
7 the celebration and encourages their participation.
8 The significance of the Oklahoma stretch of Route 66 is
9 demonstrated through its status as both a state and a National
10 Scenic Byway and as a segment of the Route 66 National Historic
11 Trail (legislation for NHT designation is pending in the U.S.
12 Congress). Dozens of Oklahoma properties are related to Route 66,
13 such as roadbed segments, bridges, commercial buildings, service
14 stations and tourist attractions, and are listed in the National
15 Register of Historic Places. The significance of the highway is
16 further recognized through the National Trust for Historic
17 Preservation's selection of the entire length of the highway as one
18 of its National Treasures.
19 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 4020.2, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 4020.2. A. The Oklahoma Route 66 Centennial Forward
22 Commission shall be composed of twenty-one (21) members. Appointed
23 members shall reflect the interests, history and importance of the
24
Req. No. 16828 Page 3

1 comm unities along Route 66 in Oklahoma. The members are appointed
2 as follows:
3 1. Two members shall be appointed by the Speaker of the House
4 of Representatives;
5 2. Two members shall be appointed by the President Pro Tempore
6 of the Senate;
7 3. Three members of the public shall be appointed by the
8 Governor; and
9 4. Fourteen ex officio members shall be appointed as follows:
10 a. the Governor or his or her designee,
11 b. the Lieutenant Governor, who shall serve as
12 chairperson, or his or her designee,
13 c. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Department of
14 Transportation or his or her designee,
15 d. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Historical
16 Society or his or her designee,
17 e. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Department of
18 Commerce or his or her designee,
19 f. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Tourism and
20 Recreation Department or his or her designee,
21 g. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Arts Council or
22 his or her designee,
23 h. the President of the Route 66 Alliance or his or her
24 designee,
Req. No. 16828 Page 4

1 i. the President of the Oklahoma Route 66 Association or
2 his or her designee,
3 j. the Executive Director of Preservation Oklahoma, Inc.,
4 or his or her designee,
5 k. the Executive Director of the Oklahoma Museums
6 Association or his or her designee,
7 l. the Executive Director of Oklahoma Humanities or his
8 or her designee,
9 m. the Director of the Oklahoma Municipal League or his
10 or her designee, and
11 n. the President of the Oklahoma State Chamber of
12 Commerce or his or her designee.
13 An ex officio member of the Commission vacates the person's position
14 on the Commission if the person ceases to hold the position that
15 qualifies the person for service on the Commission.
16 B. The Commission shall meet at least quarterly at the times
17 and places in this state that the Commission designates. A majority
18 of the members of the Commission constitutes a quorum for
19 transacting Commission business. Subject to appropriation, the
20 Oklahoma Historical Society shall provide administrative and other
21 support to the Commission.
22 C. The Commission shall:
23
24
Req. No. 16828 Page 5

1 1. Plan and sponsor official Route 66 Centennial events,
2 programs and activities appropriate to commemorate the Route 66
3 Centennial;
4 2. Encourage the development of programs designed to involve
5 all citizens in activities that commemorate the Route 66 Centennial
6 events; and
7 3. Make available to the public, to the best of the
8 Commission's ability, information on Route 66 Centennial events
9 happening throughout the State of Oklahoma.
10 D. The Commission may accept monetary gifts, grants or
11 appropriations from any public or private source to be held in a
12 nonappropriated revolving fund authorized for the Oklahoma
13 Historical Society and expended solely for the use of the Commission
14 in performing the Commission's powers and duties under this act.
15 The Commission may also accept in-kind gifts.
16 E. Each member of the Commission shall serve without
17 compensation or reimbursement for travel related to Commission
18 duties, aside from the compensation he or she might otherwise
19 receive as authorized by law.
20 F. The Commission shall be dissolved on June 30, 2027 June 30,
21 2030, and any assets remaining in the Commission's trust fund shall
22 be deposited into the state's General Revenue Fund. A final report
23 on the activities of the Oklahoma Route 66 Centennial Forward
24
